Aung San Suu Kyi, the Burmese Nobel Peace laureate, may be the most spied-on, or surveilled, human being on earth.
The authorities have arrested hundreds of her party members and prevented Suu Kyi from meeting with journalists and diplomats.
State Law and Order Restoration Council--which took over Burma in 1988 and changed its name to Myanmar, sees Suu Kyi as a primary threat.
